  <title translate="true">ActiveOnLayer</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">ActiveOnLayer</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para style="margin-bottom:10px; line-height:2.0;"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">ActiveOnLayer</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">For MODFLOW and PHAST models, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">ActiveOnLayer</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">(Layer) returns true if the Active data set has a value of true at the current column and row on the specified layer. </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">ActiveOnLayer</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is used in the formula for the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">UZF_Layer</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> data set in MODFLOW. </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">ActiveOnLayer</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> can &#160;only be used when it is being evaluated at cells (MODFLOW) or elements (PHAST). &#160;It can not be used when it is being evaluated at nodes in PHAST. In SUTRA models, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">ActiveOnLayer</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> always returns true.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
